      <section eId="sec_514">
        <num>514</num>
        <heading>Agreements for purchase by a corporation of its own shares</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_514__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>An agreement for the purchase by a corporation of its own shares\nshall be enforceable by the shareholder and the corporation to the\nextent such purchase is permitted at the time of purchase by section 513\n(Purchase or redemption by a corporation of its own shares).\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_514__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The possibility that a corporation may not be able to purchase its\nshares under section 513 shall not be a ground for denying to either\nparty specific performance of an agreement for the purchase by a\ncorporation of its own shares, if at the time for performance the\ncorporation can purchase all or part of such shares under section 513.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
